The test still fails with EADDRINUSE. Two issues found:

1. **100ms port release delay is too short** - Increase to 500ms in afterEach
2. **Untracked server instances** - Tests in "createHttpHookServer" describe block (lines 99-113) create servers but don't assign to `server` variable, so afterEach can't clean them up

**Required changes** in `node/tests/http-hook-server.test.ts`:

```typescript
// Change afterEach delay from 100ms to 500ms:
afterEach(async () => {
  if (server) {
    try {
      await server.stop();
      server = null as any;
    } catch (err) {
      console.warn('Failed to stop server:', err);
    }
  }
  // Increased delay for port release (100ms → 500ms)
  await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 500));
});
```

Also add cleanup for createHttpHookServer tests:
```typescript
describe('createHttpHookServer', () => {
  let tempServer: HttpHookServer | null = null;

  afterEach(async () => {
    if (tempServer) {
      try {
        await tempServer.stop();
      } catch {}
      tempServer = null;
    }
  });

  it('should create an HttpHookServer instance', () => {
    tempServer = createHttpHookServer({ port: testPort });
    expect(tempServer).toBeDefined();
    expect(tempServer).toBeInstanceOf(HttpHookServer);
  });

  // Similar for other tests in this block...
});
```

Please apply these fixes and re-run tests.

